        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 2:26PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 226 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
New Paris, or near Goshen, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Coldwater, Bronson, Quincy, Litchfield, Girard, Batavia, Sherwood,
Allen, South Butler, Matteson Lake, and Hodunk.

This includes Interstate 69 in Michigan between mile markers 9 and
21.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
